articles.description: Iowa State freshman Lindell Wigginton upstaged Trae Young by scoring 26 points and the Cyclones upset No. 17 Oklahoma 88-80 on Saturday, handing the Sooners their sixth consecutive road loss.
articles.headline: Iowa State upsets No. 17 Oklahoma 88-80

images.caption: Lindell Wigginton joins Doug Sherman and Robbie Hummel after his 26 points helped take down Trae Young and the No. 17 Sooners.
images.name: Wigginton key for Cyclones in victory over OU

articles.description: Justin Pierce scored a career-high 33 points on 10-of-15 shooting and William & Mary broke away from Delaware in the second half for an 83-66 victory on Saturday.
articles.headline: William & Mary downs Delaware 83-66 as Pierce scores 33

articles.description: Luke Maye scores 33 points and grabs 17 rebounds in North Carolina's 96-89 victory over NC State.
articles.headline: Maye's double-double lifts UNC to 3rd straight win

images.caption: Luke Maye scores 33 points and grabs 17 rebounds in North Carolina's 96-89 victory over NC State.
images.name: Maye's double-double lifts UNC to 3rd straight win

articles.description: Vladimir Brodziansky scored 25 points, Kouat Noi had his second straight career high with 18 and TCU won an important matchup between teams battling for the NCAA Tournament, beating Texas 87-71 on Saturday.
articles.headline: TCU cruises past Texas 87-71 in matchup of NCAA hopefuls

articles.description: Shawn Anderson and Evan Weick scored 16 of their combined 25 points in the second half and Tom Lacey finished with 10 points and nine rebounds to help Navy beat Army 68-59 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Navy leads wire-to-wire in 68-59 win over Army

videos.description: Deandre Ayton kicks it out to Parker Jackson-Cartwright, who drains the 3-pointer from the wing.
videos.headline: Arizona's Jackson-Cartwright swishes in 3-pointer

videos.description: Allonzo Trier takes it to the basket and drives in for a layup.
videos.headline: Arizona's Trier drives in for a great layup

videos.description: Coming off a timeout, Allonzo Trier lobs it up to Deandre Ayton for an alley-oop dunk.
videos.headline: Arizona's Ayton slams down a dunk

videos.description: Parker Jackson-Cartwright finds Keanu Pinder who takes it home with a dunk.
videos.headline: Arizona's Pinder throws down one-handed slam in transition

videos.description: Abu Kigab denies an Arizona shot attempt, Troy Brown gets the rebound and passes it to Victor Bailey Jr., who lays it in to make it a 3 point game.
videos.headline: Ducks take it home with a dunk in transition

videos.description: Wildcats head coach Sean Miller loses his cool after officials call the ball out of bounds on Arizona, when it appeared to go off an Oregon player.
videos.headline: Arizona coach furious with ref's call

videos.description: MiKyle McIntosh makes an easy layup and is amped up.
videos.headline: Oregon's McIntosh hyped after layup

videos.description: Paul White gets the rebound and kicks it to Elijah Brown who drains the 3-pointer from the corner.
videos.headline: Oregon's Brown sinks open 3-pointer to tie game

videos.description: Oregon's Troy Brown sinks a 3-pointer from the wing and Arizona's Parker Jackson-Cartwright counters by draining a 3 from the top of the arc.
videos.headline: Ducks-Wildcats keeping game close with back-to-back 3s.

videos.description: Allonzo Trier goes in for the drive but gets rejected by MiKyle McIntosh, who jumps over him to block the shot.
videos.headline: Ducks' McIntosh jumps over player to deny lay-in attempt

videos.description: Allonzo Trier lobs it up to Deandre Ayton who makes the one-handed dunk for a 1 point lead.
videos.headline: Wildcats' Ayton slams it home to take the lead
